02:15.933 --> 02:18.049
This is wrong.
There has to be a way we could...

02:18.213 --> 02:19.931
We could cut the power
as a diversion.

02:20.093 --> 02:23.608
She has hundreds of followers in there
acting with a single, focused will.

02:23.773 --> 02:25.764
We can't risk going against that.

02:26.093 --> 02:27.367
Not now. Someone...

02:34.973 --> 02:36.247
ANGEL:
Drive.

02:36.413 --> 02:39.610
- We can't just leave him. He's your...
- I know what he is. Wes, drive.

03:10.133 --> 03:11.964
Sacrifice

03:55.893 --> 03:57.212
[WOMAN SPEAKING
OVER RADIO]

03:57.413 --> 03:59.973
<i>And in an impromptu speech today,</i>
<i>the mayor...</i>

04:00.133 --> 04:01.885
<i>I really love that guy, don 't you?</i>

04:02.053 --> 04:05.602
<i>The mayor declared Los Angeles</i>
<i>the First Citadel of Jasmine...</i>

04:05.773 --> 04:10.164
<i>... a cradle of civilization which will</i>
<i>usher in a new age for all humanity.</i>

04:10.333 --> 04:14.372
<i>In related news, the L.A. Archdiocese</i>
<i>has stated to the press...</i>

04:14.533 --> 04:17.252
<i>... that it will remove all false idols</i>
<i>from its churches...</i>

04:17.413 --> 04:21.122
<i>... replacing them with images</i>
<i>of She Who Walks Among Us.</i>

04:21.293 --> 04:23.170
<i>Way to go, Catholic Church.</i>

04:23.493 --> 04:26.326
Well, talk about media bias.

04:26.493 --> 04:30.611
Not that I want to talk about media bias.
Seems rather moot right now.

04:30.773 --> 04:32.491
Speaking of moot, what about us?

04:32.653 --> 04:35.645
Anyone else feel like
the last feisty wife in Stepford?

04:35.853 --> 04:38.606
What are we gonna do?
What can we do?

04:38.773 --> 04:40.252
There has to be an answer.

04:40.413 --> 04:42.005
There has to be a way.
We need time.

04:42.173 --> 04:44.403
To hell with that.
We need a damn break.

04:44.613 --> 04:48.208
But the universe don't seem to be
handing breaks out to underdogs lately.

04:48.373 --> 04:51.251
No leads, no database,
no weapons, no shelter.

04:51.453 --> 04:52.727
Very little gas.

04:53.013 --> 04:56.050
We should have taken Connor with us.
He looks...

04:56.373 --> 04:58.603
What if he doesn't wake up?

04:59.573 --> 05:01.609
What if we took him and he did?

05:07.413 --> 05:10.689
JASMINE:
Thank you. Now, please come to me.

05:30.533 --> 05:31.852
Connor...

05:32.573 --> 05:33.926
...you're awake.

05:36.013 --> 05:37.332
You're...

05:39.333 --> 05:40.846
...indescribable.

05:41.533 --> 05:43.012
I know.

05:57.333 --> 05:59.449
They tried to turn me against you.

06:00.693 --> 06:04.242
They cut me.
Rubbed blood into the wound.

06:04.413 --> 06:07.450
The hateful always have one
or two wretched tricks to play.

06:10.453 --> 06:14.412
You must rest now.
We have nothing to fear from them.

06:14.573 --> 06:17.041
They are alone.
We are many.

06:17.573 --> 06:19.962
But Gunn
and Wesley and Lorne.

06:20.573 --> 06:22.131
They've all been turned.

06:22.293 --> 06:25.524
- We have to stop whatever they're...
- We will.

06:26.013 --> 06:29.608
Connor, there's
nothing they can do.

06:30.213 --> 06:34.126
Every moment that passes,
I grow closer to my followers.

06:34.853 --> 06:38.289
I feel what they feel,
I see what they see.

06:39.653 --> 06:42.645
We're fusing together
like the cells of a single body.

06:43.653 --> 06:46.963
They're my eyes,
my skin, my limbs...

06:47.133 --> 06:48.964
...and if need be...

06:49.133 --> 06:51.203
...my fists.

07:11.333 --> 07:13.767
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

07:17.293 --> 07:21.650
- I don't know. It's a lot of pod people.
- It's better than the last three places.

07:21.813 --> 07:24.008
We won't make it out
of the city without gas.

07:24.213 --> 07:26.283
So that's our big plan?
Just keep running?

07:26.453 --> 07:27.966
I hear good things about Belize.

07:28.173 --> 07:31.609
If we could get out of the sphere
of her influence, we could warn people...

07:31.773 --> 07:33.445
...prepare some form of resistance.

07:33.613 --> 07:36.047
Look at them. They're all so happy.

07:36.213 --> 07:40.047
Yeah, they'll be happier when they're
gouging out our eyes and stomping us.

07:40.373 --> 07:43.445
- That's why we have to do this fast.
- Fast works for me.

07:43.733 --> 07:45.883
Gunn, they're just under her spell.

07:46.053 --> 07:48.772
But if it does come down
to a choice between us or them...

07:48.933 --> 07:50.764
Believe me, I'm there.

07:55.973 --> 07:58.009
Sorry, bro, it's for your own good.

08:00.133 --> 08:03.443
That's right. It's the big bad
Free Will Gang gassing up.

08:03.613 --> 08:05.251
ANGEL:
We don't wanna hurt anybody.

08:05.533 --> 08:08.331
JASMINE'S VOICE: But you are
hurting them, Angel, just by being.

08:09.133 --> 08:11.010
Okay, that's new.

08:11.293 --> 08:14.603
You're a disease in the body Jasmine,
and you'll be purged.

08:17.813 --> 08:19.531
Soccer mom, 12:00!

08:23.213 --> 08:24.532
[SPEAKING IN
JASMINE'S VOICE]

08:24.693 --> 08:27.730
You can't outrun my love.
It has wings made of radio.

08:31.293 --> 08:32.611
[SPEAKING IN
JASMINE'S VOICE]

08:32.813 --> 08:36.852
My love sings over the wires
that bind this world.

08:37.293 --> 08:39.249
Okay, getting a little creepy.

08:39.413 --> 08:42.688
JASMINE'S VOICE: The city is mine,
vampire. All its tools are mine.

08:42.852 --> 08:44.491
Yeah, we're working on that.

08:44.653 --> 08:46.928
Okay, pit stop's over. Let's go.

08:49.213 --> 08:51.329
No snacks? I thought snacks were...

08:54.453 --> 08:56.444
[SIRENS WAILING]

09:01.613 --> 09:04.411
[JASMINE LAUGHING]

09:19.493 --> 09:21.609
Never seen so many cruisers.

09:21.773 --> 09:23.331
We're the only criminals left.

09:23.493 --> 09:26.451
No way we're driving out of this.
It's time we disappeared.

09:40.093 --> 09:43.290
Yeah, I'm moving, Angel-cakes.
Might not look like it. But inside...

09:43.493 --> 09:45.882
...where it counts,
I'm running full speed ahead.

09:46.053 --> 09:48.362
Won't take them long to figure out.

09:52.173 --> 09:53.447
One minute.

09:53.613 --> 09:56.411
No one under her control
knows these tunnels better than you.

09:56.573 --> 09:58.768
- It should buy us some time.
GUNN: Time to do what?

09:58.933 --> 10:01.970
Get all stanky and starve to death?
I mean, what are we doing?

10:02.133 --> 10:04.408
I don't know what we'll do.
I don't have a plan.

10:04.573 --> 10:07.610
This whole "Jasmine world order" thing
took me by surprise.

10:07.773 --> 10:09.843
- I ain't eating no rats.
- Good, neither am I.

10:10.013 --> 10:13.085
- All right, plan's coming together.
- Glad to see you're on board.

10:14.053 --> 10:17.090
Oh, God, all the chasing
and the chaos...

10:17.253 --> 10:20.484
- Cordelia.
- I can't believe I almost forgot about her.

10:21.013 --> 10:22.969
Do it.

10:23.973 --> 10:26.009
Forget about her.

10:26.213 --> 10:28.522
We all have to now.
We don't have a choice.

10:29.733 --> 10:31.724
The minute's up.

10:44.093 --> 10:46.084
[SKITTERING]

10:59.973 --> 11:01.247
Connor.

11:03.333 --> 11:04.607
CONNOR:
Look.

11:04.813 --> 11:07.281
JASMINE:
I know. I saw it through you.

11:07.453 --> 11:09.648
It was them, wasn't it?

11:12.013 --> 11:14.811
It horrifies me to see
what they're capable of...

11:15.613 --> 11:18.002
...how far they've let their hate
take them.

11:19.893 --> 11:22.282
They cut into her
while she lay sleeping.

11:23.573 --> 11:26.292
Her precious blood stolen...

11:26.453 --> 11:30.731
...for their black, deceitful,
cowardly magic.

11:31.493 --> 11:33.961
They're always using magic.

11:35.893 --> 11:37.167
Leave me.

11:38.413 --> 11:41.166
I want to be alone with my mother.

12:07.413 --> 12:10.689
You look a little down, sugarplum.
Is it Cordy?

12:12.253 --> 12:16.610
- I can't. I don't care what he says.
- I know, kitten.

12:16.773 --> 12:19.890
But underneath that blood-feeding,
creature-of-the-night facade...

12:20.053 --> 12:22.328
...he's heartless lately.
ANGEL: Hearts get in the way.

12:22.493 --> 12:25.326
- Hearing as good as ever, though.
ANGEL: If we don't gut ourselves...

12:25.493 --> 12:29.372
...burn out everything inside that gave
her power over us, then we're lost.

12:29.733 --> 12:32.805
LORNE: I hate to say it,
but I've been lost for, like, two hours.

12:34.693 --> 12:36.206
Still, I miss her.

12:36.693 --> 12:39.571
I miss the warmth
and the knowing what's right...

12:39.733 --> 12:42.372
...and that you're
doing it just by loving her.

12:42.533 --> 12:44.205
Tough drug to kick cold turkey.

12:44.453 --> 12:48.810
I remember the first time she took me
aside, that fight at the bowling alley.

12:50.333 --> 12:55.202
Me, pale, frail Winifred Burkle,
sitting with a goddess.

12:55.373 --> 12:57.329
She was asking me
what her name should be.

12:57.493 --> 13:01.486
It seems strange now,
a being of her immeasurable age...

13:01.653 --> 13:03.484
...you'd think
she'd already have a name.

13:03.653 --> 13:06.292
Maybe it was embarrassing,
like Hester or Peanut.

13:07.493 --> 13:09.324
[YELLING]

13:14.053 --> 13:15.930
GUNN:
I gotcha.

13:16.653 --> 13:18.644
[CLANGING]

13:30.413 --> 13:31.926
- Wes.
- I'm all right.

13:32.093 --> 13:34.607
No, you're not all right
till I say you're all right.

13:34.933 --> 13:36.764
- Holly, you good?
- Yes.

13:38.253 --> 13:39.811
- Trip.
- Yeah.

13:40.373 --> 13:42.967
That ugly beastie so much
as breathes wrong, stick him.

13:43.533 --> 13:45.205
Ugly... Hey.

13:47.053 --> 13:50.329
You know, I kind of have a thing
about people pointing sharp, wooden...

13:51.853 --> 13:53.332
Give me that.

14:00.773 --> 14:03.048
Enough! Enough.

14:04.293 --> 14:05.885
- You okay?
- Yeah.

14:06.093 --> 14:09.165
- It's okay. They're not under her power.
- Her who?

14:09.333 --> 14:11.403
- We'll ask the questions.
- Angel, are you sure?

14:11.573 --> 14:15.202
They're not fighting like a well-oiled,
mind-controlled army of love, are they?

14:15.373 --> 14:17.648
- No, more like a bunch of little punks.
- Punks?

14:17.813 --> 14:19.451
Gunn, let him go.

14:22.933 --> 14:24.207
Gunn?

14:27.013 --> 14:29.652
- Charles Gunn.
- I say you could use my name?

14:29.813 --> 14:32.486
I say you could use my ride
without paying the piper?

14:32.653 --> 14:34.803
What? Paying the...?

14:36.133 --> 14:39.205
Tommy Golden's little brother?
Randall?

14:39.373 --> 14:41.091
Little ass Randall Golden.

14:41.253 --> 14:43.483
This punk stole my car
when he was 12 years old.

14:44.173 --> 14:47.609
- What are you doing down here, man?
- Like I said, son, we'll ask the questions.

14:47.773 --> 14:49.764
[SKITTERING, MOANING]

14:52.893 --> 14:55.646
Starting with, what the hell was that?

14:56.093 --> 14:57.685
It's back.

15:13.453 --> 15:14.806
I'm sorry.

15:16.573 --> 15:18.131
I just couldn't be...

15:21.253 --> 15:22.527
Cordy?

15:23.013 --> 15:27.643
Connor, Cordelia's blood
is a danger to us.

15:27.813 --> 15:30.566
If she falls into hateful hands,
the hate can spread.

15:30.733 --> 15:34.362
- But where is she?
- She's where I want her to be.

15:41.613 --> 15:43.683
And so are you.

15:44.813 --> 15:46.405
Now, come.

15:51.933 --> 15:53.207
Connor.

16:08.573 --> 16:11.610
GUNN: Wow. Really like what
you've done with the place.

16:11.933 --> 16:13.764
LORNE:
Yes, this is homey.

16:21.573 --> 16:23.723
ANGEL:
So it's secure?

16:23.893 --> 16:25.929
It's held so far.

16:26.293 --> 16:27.612
Uh-huh.

16:29.453 --> 16:31.091
Held against what?

16:31.253 --> 16:34.165
Don't know exactly.
Never have gotten a clean shot.

16:34.333 --> 16:36.085
It's not like anything I've ever seen.

16:36.253 --> 16:39.051
Golden's brother used to soldier
in my crew back in the days.

16:39.213 --> 16:40.692
Then he broke off and went solo.

16:40.853 --> 16:43.083
Tommy was running our unit
when the sun went out.

16:43.253 --> 16:46.484
We stayed topside as long as we could,
tried to hold some ground...

16:46.893 --> 16:48.531
...but there were too many of them.

16:48.693 --> 16:51.571
We go out every day
to check the tracks...

16:53.133 --> 16:58.526
They're your crew, aren't they?
You're the leader.

16:58.693 --> 16:59.967
I'm Matthew.

17:02.613 --> 17:06.571
It's okay. All the other ways in
are grated off.

17:07.173 --> 17:08.652
We checked.

17:08.813 --> 17:11.281
Well, now I'm checking.

17:13.853 --> 17:15.491
He's so young.

17:15.653 --> 17:19.726
We found him in a pileup on La Brea.
Vamps laid tire traps on the road...

17:19.893 --> 17:22.123
...having themselves
a car-wreck picnic.

17:22.772 --> 17:24.411
He watched them murder his parents.

17:24.573 --> 17:26.689
They were coming after him
when we showed up.

17:31.053 --> 17:34.125
Matthew, you got any water
in this place?

17:34.293 --> 17:36.932
Yes. We tapped a clean water pipe
right over here.

17:42.533 --> 17:44.012
Anyway, I knew about this place.

17:44.173 --> 17:46.846
Used to crash up here nights
when the missions were full.

17:47.013 --> 17:50.483
So we hit a supermarket that hadn't
burnt down yet and got some supplies.

17:50.733 --> 17:52.928
We went under.
Been down here ever since.

17:53.093 --> 17:54.572
About two weeks and some change.

17:54.733 --> 17:56.405
No offense,
but two weeks here...

17:56.573 --> 17:58.689
...and I'd be ready to move back
with my mother.

17:58.853 --> 18:00.571
Yeah, well, we were holding our own.

18:00.733 --> 18:04.169
Occasional baddie looking for a place
to sleep. Nothing we couldn't handle.

18:04.333 --> 18:07.052
Till that thing out there
moved into our territory.

18:07.213 --> 18:09.169
It's been picking us off ever since.

18:09.653 --> 18:13.646
It got Tommy almost a week ago.
He was out resetting the traps.

18:21.413 --> 18:22.732
Whose blood is that?

18:24.453 --> 18:26.011
Somebody I knew.

18:31.733 --> 18:34.930
Somebody who tried
to do bad stuff to my friends.

18:38.653 --> 18:41.963
- I can't believe you stayed down here.
HOLLY: Worse up there, ain't it?

18:42.293 --> 18:45.729
The world is ending.
What does it matter where we go?

18:45.893 --> 18:50.569
Besides, whatever that evil son
of a bitch is, it killed our people...

18:51.013 --> 18:54.688
...it killed my brother.
We're going to kill him right back.

18:56.173 --> 19:00.803
It's weird, really, us running
into you like this. I mean, we...

19:02.253 --> 19:04.687
We're professional monster killers.

19:08.373 --> 19:09.886
Or we were.

19:10.053 --> 19:12.886
Are, Fred. We are.

19:13.893 --> 19:18.125
- Hey! That belonged to Tommy.
- Now it belongs to me.

19:18.293 --> 19:21.365
Let's go get professional
on this evil son of a bitch's ass.

19:24.373 --> 19:25.931
I heard that.

19:26.093 --> 19:27.412
JASMINE:
<i>Yeah.</i>

19:27.813 --> 19:31.044
Of course. Drop by anytime.

19:31.573 --> 19:33.245
Thank you for calling.

19:38.013 --> 19:40.083
Police lost them hours ago.

19:41.093 --> 19:44.051
Let me go out.
I'll bring them down, I promise.

19:44.253 --> 19:48.292
Soon. Soon you'll go out
with all of my strength behind you.

19:49.133 --> 19:51.442
But first, we have to celebrate.

19:52.213 --> 19:55.728
That was the governor on the phone,
very agreeable.

19:55.973 --> 19:58.771
He's dissolving
his administration tonight.

19:59.373 --> 20:01.489
The time of the politician is over.

20:01.653 --> 20:04.121
This state now answers to me.

20:07.693 --> 20:12.289
Oh, it's happening.
Don't you feel it?

20:13.253 --> 20:19.647
This world is about to kneel before me
and shed all its avarice, all its woe.

20:19.813 --> 20:23.203
I will free them from the Loneliness...

20:25.613 --> 20:28.525
...from the empty horror of their lives.

20:31.773 --> 20:33.525
They won't know what hit them.

20:34.293 --> 20:36.090
I'm sure of that.

20:36.253 --> 20:39.802
And you'll be there at my side.

20:40.413 --> 20:44.531
We will live in a palace built
by the love of billions.

20:44.693 --> 20:48.732
It will make the Pyramids of Giza look
like headstones in a pauper's graveyard.

20:50.813 --> 20:52.963
We'll be a family, Connor.

20:54.253 --> 20:58.292
Together, as one, forever.

20:59.333 --> 21:02.086
It's going to be beautiful.

21:02.293 --> 21:03.567
Yes.

21:10.453 --> 21:12.409
Then why aren't you smiling?

21:19.853 --> 21:21.411
I don't know.

21:21.813 --> 21:23.963
I think I do.

21:26.013 --> 21:28.652
To belong,
to truly be a part of something...

21:28.813 --> 21:32.283
...you have to surrender
to it completely.

21:33.813 --> 21:37.931
- Cordelia has done that, but you...
- I want to, really.

21:38.573 --> 21:41.883
There's a part of you
that you've kept from me.

21:42.653 --> 21:44.325
Your pain.

21:45.133 --> 21:46.646
I don't understand.

21:47.253 --> 21:50.404
Pain has been the only constant
in your life.

21:50.733 --> 21:54.203
The one thing
that has never abandoned you.

21:58.773 --> 22:04.484
You think that pain is yours
to keep and bear alone.

22:05.093 --> 22:06.572
But it's not.

22:10.373 --> 22:11.772
I want it.

22:13.093 --> 22:17.371
I want everything you are, Connor.

22:19.893 --> 22:21.485
Father.

22:22.893 --> 22:24.292
Let it go.

22:26.133 --> 22:27.930
Let me have it.

22:31.733 --> 22:33.325
Okay.

22:41.173 --> 22:42.526
Okay.

22:50.093 --> 22:52.448
FRED: They're just kids.
- Strength in numbers.

22:52.613 --> 22:54.490
- Angel...
- They just want to strike back...

22:54.653 --> 22:57.326
...at something, anything.
I know how they feel.

22:57.493 --> 22:59.609
I ever tell you I suck at sports?

23:05.333 --> 23:07.927
This is where Tommy got taken.

23:08.253 --> 23:10.721
- What's that smell?
- It's ammonia.

23:10.893 --> 23:12.485
[GROWLING, YELLING]

23:12.693 --> 23:14.206
MATTHEW:
Golden!

23:16.293 --> 23:18.284
[SWORD CLASHING]

23:30.573 --> 23:32.450
ANGEL:
Matthew, it's okay.

23:32.613 --> 23:34.126
Matt!

23:34.293 --> 23:35.612
Matthew!

23:35.773 --> 23:37.764
[SCREAMING]

23:38.973 --> 23:40.964
[SKITTERING, WHINING]

23:42.133 --> 23:44.442
Golden? Sweetie.

23:44.613 --> 23:47.650
- Lf Matthew reaches the surface...
- We'll get him. Come on!

23:47.813 --> 23:49.087
FRED:
Matthew!

23:49.493 --> 23:52.007
That thing is really pissing me off.
Lorne, Wes.

23:52.173 --> 23:55.006
- Yeah?
- Where's Wes?

24:01.693 --> 24:04.127
We loved her first.

24:10.053 --> 24:12.567
LORNE: It got Wes?
- It must have looped around behind us.

24:12.733 --> 24:15.486
It knows these tunnels better than me,
and it's fast.

24:15.693 --> 24:18.844
I'll track it down.
Lorne, take the others back to the fort.

24:19.013 --> 24:21.527
- Wait for Gunn and Fred.
- Lf you insist.

24:21.933 --> 24:24.811
Uh-uh, Dracula, not okay.

24:29.253 --> 24:31.847
All right, fine, you loved her first.

24:32.173 --> 24:35.802
Before your kind was,
my kind loved her.

24:35.973 --> 24:40.012
Stood stone on stone, built the temple...

24:40.173 --> 24:42.323
...always making ready.

24:44.093 --> 24:46.084
[WHINING]

24:48.173 --> 24:50.607
But she came here.

24:51.413 --> 24:53.051
She?

24:53.573 --> 24:56.690
- Jasmine?
- Eh?

24:56.853 --> 24:59.765
Jasmine. That's what we call her.

25:00.093 --> 25:03.642
The superior being...

25:04.493 --> 25:06.290
...that you loved first.

25:06.973 --> 25:09.692
You name her. You filthy little mice!

25:10.653 --> 25:13.451
She is the Devourer...

25:15.293 --> 25:17.523
...the song...

25:18.053 --> 25:21.284
...the peace, the whole.

25:25.333 --> 25:29.246
And you try to name her.

25:35.373 --> 25:37.682
Work to do.

25:38.493 --> 25:40.324
We loved her first.

25:55.733 --> 25:59.043
And how does your kind define love?

25:59.573 --> 26:02.770
Same as all bodies.
Same as everywheres.

26:04.893 --> 26:06.963
Love is sacrifice.

26:07.613 --> 26:08.932
GUNN:
<i>Matthew!</i>

26:09.653 --> 26:11.689
- Matthew!
FRED: Matthew?

26:12.093 --> 26:15.005
- You sure he went this way?
- Heard splashing. It's gotta be him.

26:15.173 --> 26:17.368
Unless it was one
of those skittering creatures.

26:17.533 --> 26:20.286
Well, it better skitter out of my way.
I ain't in the mood.

26:20.453 --> 26:22.762
FRED:
Or it could just be rats.

26:24.293 --> 26:26.853
Now, what did you have to go
and say that for? Damn!

26:27.013 --> 26:28.571
Sorry, I wasn't...

26:28.773 --> 26:31.970
I'm sure if it's not Matthew,
it's probably some horrible monster...

26:32.133 --> 26:34.203
...but definitely not...
- Look at us...

26:34.733 --> 26:37.452
...where we are.
I mean, yesterday we were happy.

26:37.613 --> 26:40.810
Happier than I thought possible.
Now we're trudging through sewage...

26:40.973 --> 26:43.362
...hunting some kid to drag him
back down here...

26:43.533 --> 26:46.491
...so he doesn't find out
a Shangri-La-La-Land up there.

26:46.653 --> 26:49.690
He's scared, Charles.
Think how he feels.

26:49.853 --> 26:52.413
You heard Angel.
Feelings don't enter into it anymore.

26:52.573 --> 26:54.291
That the world we're fighting for?

26:54.453 --> 26:58.048
The right to be heartless
and uncaring shells, to be dead inside?

26:58.213 --> 27:00.886
We'll be dead period
if Jasmine gets a hold of that kid.

27:01.053 --> 27:04.250
- We're fighting for our survival.
- That's not enough, not for me.

27:04.413 --> 27:06.881
Maybe you can turn off your
feelings like Angel can...

27:07.053 --> 27:08.691
...leave those we care about behind.

27:08.853 --> 27:11.162
You had no trouble turning off
your emotions when...

27:11.333 --> 27:13.528
- When what?
- Nothing.

27:13.693 --> 27:15.445
- What were you gonna say?
- Forget it.

27:15.613 --> 27:18.605
- When did I ever...?
- When you and I killed a man.

27:19.733 --> 27:21.212
I mean, when I did.

27:21.893 --> 27:23.929
- We did.
- Whatever.

27:24.093 --> 27:28.086
When the circumstances called for it,
you did what you thought you had to.

27:28.253 --> 27:30.562
It didn't matter
what anybody else thought.

27:33.293 --> 27:36.683
You're right about all of it
except for one thing.

27:37.213 --> 27:40.888
What we did, I felt it...

27:41.053 --> 27:43.203
...every bit of it.

27:43.973 --> 27:46.533
Sometimes when I allow myself
to think about it...

27:46.693 --> 27:49.571
...it eats me up inside.

27:50.253 --> 27:51.652
Yeah, me too.

27:53.133 --> 27:57.524
Well, I don't know about you, but I'd
take that over being a shell any day.

28:01.933 --> 28:05.812
Come on. There's a scared kid
out there we gotta find.

28:10.373 --> 28:13.092
You think I didn't see that back there?
You're one of them.

28:13.693 --> 28:16.526
- Golden, it's not like that.
- He's telling the truth.

28:16.693 --> 28:21.084
Excuse me, not talking to horned demon,
talking to vampire. Thank you.

28:21.253 --> 28:24.802
All right, what you saw,
yes, I can't deny that.

28:24.973 --> 28:27.851
- But he only drinks pig's blood.
- Lorne.

28:28.013 --> 28:30.652
It's true. You gotta give
an undead fella points for that.

28:30.813 --> 28:33.646
Unless you're into the whole
kosher thing, but you're not...

28:33.813 --> 28:37.601
Well, you don't look...
Okay, horned demon shutting up.

28:37.773 --> 28:40.128
I don't blame you
for feeling this way...

28:40.293 --> 28:42.682
...but I'm not going
to justify my existence to you.

28:42.853 --> 28:46.209
I wouldn't be able to.
But what I can do...

28:46.373 --> 28:49.285
...is take that spear away from you
and snap it into kindling...

28:49.493 --> 28:53.247
...and break your neck
in half the time it would take for you...

28:53.413 --> 28:55.927
...to give it a good push.

28:56.773 --> 29:00.448
Or you could step aside
and let me go help my friend.

29:03.493 --> 29:04.812
[GRUNTING]

29:40.173 --> 29:41.606
WESLEY:
That door is open.

29:42.093 --> 29:43.651
Yes.

29:43.933 --> 29:45.969
Aren't you worried I'll just run away?

29:47.053 --> 29:50.090
Not worried. Good at catching furries.

29:50.453 --> 29:53.013
Yes, clearly.

29:55.653 --> 29:57.484
So...

29:57.653 --> 30:00.213
...not from around here, are you?

30:00.773 --> 30:02.172
No.

30:04.053 --> 30:05.930
Other world.

30:06.173 --> 30:08.403
Older world.

30:14.093 --> 30:18.211
You go. Go on. Use my key, visit.

30:18.933 --> 30:22.608
What we breathing there
burn out little mouse lungs...

30:22.773 --> 30:24.729
...before you can make a peep.

30:25.333 --> 30:26.607
Fair enough.

30:26.813 --> 30:30.044
"Fair enough."
"Fair enough-enough."

30:31.773 --> 30:37.245
- Are you preparing a spell?
- This blood magic. Flesh magic.

30:37.533 --> 30:40.730
Older than words. More, much power.

30:40.893 --> 30:44.602
This magic she will hear. She will
hear and remember her true ones.

30:45.093 --> 30:48.165
- So no incantations, then?
- No words.

30:49.093 --> 30:52.927
She give no care about words.
Word magic.

30:53.093 --> 30:54.890
Really?

30:56.053 --> 30:58.203
There is only one word she...

31:02.813 --> 31:05.646
One word? What word does
she give care about?

31:05.813 --> 31:09.647
You is talking meat.
Don't make me come down there.

31:12.813 --> 31:17.091
My God. What is it with you, man?
This is disgusting.

31:17.253 --> 31:20.131
- You!
- Just drop the clich <i>e</i>, serial-killer crap...

31:20.293 --> 31:22.887
...and stake me already. Please.

31:23.053 --> 31:28.173
I tear your guts all inside out.
I stitch your guts every all over.

31:28.333 --> 31:31.086
- Why don't you go dead.
- Why don't you go fu...

31:31.773 --> 31:33.092
[YELLS]

31:35.333 --> 31:37.130
More talky meat.

31:41.973 --> 31:45.488
You can't kill him.
Not that way.

31:46.333 --> 31:48.563
He's already dead.
He's a vampire.

31:52.413 --> 31:55.564
Vampire. Like the one
with the angry steel?

31:55.733 --> 31:57.166
Angry steel?

31:57.853 --> 32:01.482
The one that hurt me
in the tunnels back there.

32:03.053 --> 32:04.691
Angel.

32:04.893 --> 32:06.212
Eh?

32:06.373 --> 32:09.490
That's his name,
the one who attacked you.

32:10.173 --> 32:14.405
You creatures, throwing your names
all over all the time.

32:14.573 --> 32:17.770
That's why you are so weak.
Too many are knowing your names.

32:18.253 --> 32:20.164
Takes your power away.

32:20.333 --> 32:23.291
It doesn't work that way here.
With us...

32:27.533 --> 32:29.683
So that's the word, isn't it?

32:29.853 --> 32:32.731
- The word she gives care about.
- Shut.

32:32.893 --> 32:35.885
- It's her name.
- Shut, shut, shut!

32:37.693 --> 32:40.127
Shut, shut, shut!

32:51.013 --> 32:52.412
FRED:
Matthew.

32:54.173 --> 32:56.971
It's okay. We don't want to hurt you.
We just want to talk...

32:57.133 --> 32:58.646
...but it's not safe here.

32:59.333 --> 33:01.608
You didn't tell me the sun
came back out.

33:01.773 --> 33:04.765
Oh, yeah, forgot to tell you.
Sun came back out.

33:05.253 --> 33:07.687
Angel, he's a vampire,
like the ones who...

33:07.853 --> 33:10.845
We can't explain it up here,
but we're the good guys, I swear.

33:11.013 --> 33:12.924
- And we need you to come with us.
- No.

33:13.213 --> 33:16.205
- No, I won't go.
- Sorry, son, but we ain't asking.

33:16.373 --> 33:18.568
Help! Help!

33:19.893 --> 33:21.167
Fred.

33:22.973 --> 33:26.363
- Fred!
- What?

33:26.533 --> 33:28.285
Get his feet.

33:30.973 --> 33:35.330
She has a name, and it has power over
her. That's why she keeps it a secret.

33:35.533 --> 33:37.808
La, la, la, la, la, la, la, la!
La, la, la, la!

33:37.973 --> 33:39.247
Not listening!

33:39.413 --> 33:42.689
And somehow, her true name prevents
her from choosing a false one...

33:42.853 --> 33:44.525
...so one of us had to do it.

33:48.973 --> 33:50.247
What it matters, eh?

33:50.413 --> 33:53.962
Eh, talky meat?
I no keep the name.

33:54.133 --> 33:56.886
High priest keep the name.

33:57.373 --> 34:00.251
And you about to go dead.

34:00.413 --> 34:03.644
About to be a smear
on my flesh spell.

34:04.733 --> 34:08.487
I just messenger
from the ones who love truly.

34:08.813 --> 34:12.692
Well, then, I guess it's time
to shoot the messenger.

34:13.092 --> 34:17.132
Or, you know, chop the messenger
into little, bitty pieces. Whatever.

34:21.853 --> 34:26.483
And that's why when we use
words like "ugly-ass" and "beastie"...

34:26.693 --> 34:29.206
...we can sometimes do more
damage than we intend to.

34:29.413 --> 34:34.009
It ain't all about sticks and stones,
my young friends. That's all.

34:34.373 --> 34:38.969
A little life lesson, one to grow on.
Knowing. Knowing is half...

34:39.132 --> 34:40.485
Shut up.

34:41.172 --> 34:42.492
HOLLY:
Matthew.

34:46.813 --> 34:49.771
GOLDEN: What the hell happened, man?
- He'll be okay.

34:51.533 --> 34:53.409
I'm sorry. We...
We had no other...

34:53.572 --> 34:55.688
- Fred.
- What is she talking about?

34:56.132 --> 34:58.727
- Nothing.
- I'm not liking what I'm not hearing.

34:58.893 --> 35:01.248
What did you do to my boy?

35:01.453 --> 35:03.569
There's a new world
of bad going on upstairs...

35:03.733 --> 35:05.689
...and your boy was walking
into it blind.

35:05.853 --> 35:08.128
We did what we had to,
and I ain't interested...

35:08.293 --> 35:10.409
...in your opinion on the subject.

35:10.613 --> 35:12.604
[LAUGHING]

35:14.493 --> 35:15.767
Matty?

35:15.933 --> 35:17.810
- Honey?
- Oh, no.

35:19.213 --> 35:20.532
[SPEAKING IN
JASMINE'S VOICE]

35:20.733 --> 35:23.406
I see you.

35:23.933 --> 35:26.811
Holly, look what they did
to Matthew.

35:26.973 --> 35:30.124
They hit him again and again
until he lost all consciousness.

35:31.613 --> 35:35.242
- He just wanted to see the sun.
- Fred, Lorne, it's time to go.

35:35.493 --> 35:39.486
Golden, my love,
don't you want to hit them?

35:39.653 --> 35:42.451
Don't you want to kill them?

35:42.613 --> 35:46.526
You know, that just might
make my whole damn day.

35:46.693 --> 35:48.490
GUNN:
Go!

36:03.013 --> 36:04.332
[SPEAKING IN
JASMINE'S VOICE]

36:04.533 --> 36:06.364
Hello again, children.

36:06.733 --> 36:08.849
I believe you've met my father.

36:16.533 --> 36:18.524
[GRUNTING]

36:21.653 --> 36:22.972
[YELLS]

36:23.173 --> 36:25.084
Little mice.

36:25.693 --> 36:28.651
They always soft inside.

36:30.173 --> 36:32.289
Wretched little...

36:34.773 --> 36:36.650
Time to go dead, mouse.

36:36.853 --> 36:38.844
[YELLING]

36:40.813 --> 36:43.122
Wait your turn, talky!

36:44.093 --> 36:45.412
[YELLS]

36:45.813 --> 36:48.247
A little soft yourself in there.

36:53.773 --> 36:57.129
Devour this meat...

36:57.493 --> 37:01.486
...I give unto thee.

37:04.093 --> 37:07.722
That creature, he came from a world
that's worshipped Jasmine for millennia.

37:07.893 --> 37:11.806
- A world that we can reach through this.
- What?

37:13.173 --> 37:16.483
I think the universe just handed us
our first break.

37:17.053 --> 37:18.486
LORNE:
I really hate today!

37:18.653 --> 37:21.486
More worried about tomorrow myself.
Come on!

37:21.813 --> 37:25.522
No inscriptions.
No markings of any kind.

37:25.893 --> 37:27.770
No moving parts, as far as I can tell.

37:27.933 --> 37:31.369
- So this high priest holds the true name.
- Exactly.

37:35.333 --> 37:37.801
What else do we know about him?

37:37.973 --> 37:40.567
I'm just guessing
that he's bigger and meaner...

37:40.733 --> 37:42.849
...than our big,
mean friend over there.

37:44.053 --> 37:46.965
Wouldn't surprise me.
What about...?

37:48.333 --> 37:50.449
Wes, something is going down.

37:50.773 --> 37:52.047
Something?

37:53.173 --> 37:55.289
Something bad.

37:55.453 --> 37:57.045
Connor.

38:06.133 --> 38:07.407
Angel.

38:10.173 --> 38:11.447
Angel.

38:11.773 --> 38:13.252
FRED: Angel.
- God, are we dead yet?

38:13.413 --> 38:14.812
ANGEL:
Guys!

38:18.773 --> 38:21.162
No words. No word magic.

38:21.893 --> 38:24.361
- Angel, it's Connor. He's here.
- I know.

38:24.533 --> 38:27.093
LORNE:
And the National Guard, I think.

38:29.373 --> 38:31.887
- No!
- No word magic. Powerless.

38:32.053 --> 38:34.169
Much more power...

38:34.813 --> 38:36.451
...in blood magic.

38:44.333 --> 38:45.607
WESLEY:
Angel, I got it!

38:47.933 --> 38:51.369
- Okay, I'll hold it. You guys, get going.
- No, we can't go, only you.

38:51.533 --> 38:53.091
ANGEL:
What are you talking about?

38:54.413 --> 38:56.881
That thing's world,
the atmosphere will kill us.

38:58.253 --> 39:00.084
We can't help there.

39:00.253 --> 39:03.563
But someone who knows the truth
has to live through this.

39:03.733 --> 39:07.009
- Angel, that's you.
- I can't.

39:08.053 --> 39:10.726
Hearts get in the way, right?

39:17.733 --> 39:19.769
Angel, wait!

39:31.573 --> 39:34.292
- We can't hold it.
- Time for the big fight scene.

39:34.493 --> 39:35.846
CONNOR:
Move aside.

39:36.013 --> 39:39.323
Count of three.
One. Two.

40:18.493 --> 40:20.484
[SKITTERING]

40:33.133 --> 40:34.691
Oh, hell.

